            RosePad Privacy Policy
         Last Updated: March 26, 2025
1. Introduction
  Welcome to RosePad. This Privacy Policy describes how we handle information in our simple text editor application. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about data handling.
2. Information We Collect
  2.1 Local Data Storage
    RosePad is designed to be a privacy-first application. All notes and data are stored locally on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or store any of your personal information or note contents on external servers.
3. Data Security
  We prioritize the security of your data through:
  - Local-only storage
  - No cloud synchronization
  - Local data storage protection
  - Regular security updates
4. User Control
  You have complete control over your data:
  - All notes are stored locally on your device
  - You can delete notes at any time
  - You can export or backup your notes as you choose
5. Third-Party Services
  RosePad does not integrate with any third-party cloud services or data collection platforms. The application is a standalone text editor focused on local, private note-taking.
6. User Accessibility
  RosePad is a simple text editor accessible to users of all ages. We believe in providing a straightforward, user-friendly tool for writing and note-taking.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
  We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new privacy policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
8. Contact Us
  If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at alex.goranov8@gmail.com.
9. Consent
  By using RosePad, you consent to the terms of this privacy policy.
10. Legal Compliance
  This privacy policy is designed to comply with general data protection regulations and aims to be transparent about our data handling practices.
